<section xml:id="sec_ls_summ">
  <title>Summary</title>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>
        A least squares approximation to
        <m>A \vx = \vb</m> is found by orthogonally projecting <m>\vb</m> onto <m>\Col A</m>.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        If the columns of <m>A</m> are linearly independent,
        then the least squares approximation to
        <m>A \vx = \vb</m> is <m>\left(A^{\tr}A\right)^{-1}A^{\tr} \vb</m>.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        The least squares solution to <m>A \vx = \vb</m>,
        where <m>A\vx = [y_1 \ y_2 \ \ldots \ y_m]</m> and <m>\vb = [b_1 \ b_2 \ \ldots \ b_ m]^{\tr}</m>,
        minimizes the distance <m>||A\vx - \vb||</m>, where
        <me>
          ||A\vx - \vb||^2 = (y_1-b_1)^2 + (y_2-b_2)^2 + \cdots + (y_m-b_m)^2
        </me>.
        So the least squares solution minimizes a sum of squares.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>